  }} }} .]] 'Pyrene' is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon (PAH) consisting of
  four fused benzene rings, resulting in a flat aromatic system. The chemical
  formula is . This colorless solid is the smallest peri-fused PAH (one where
  the rings are fused through more than one face). Pyrene forms during
  incomplete combustion of organic compounds.
